title.narrative: Feed the Future Ethiopia Livelihoods for Resilience Activity - Oromia

description.narrative: (Ethiopia): The Feed the Future Livelihoods for Resilience-Oromia (LRO), implemented by Catholic Relief Services, builds resilient livelihoods with improved food and nutrition security for 24,500 chronically food-insecure households in the Oromia Region with the goal of graduating beneficiaries from USG assistance. The activity complements the three PSNP livelihood pathways (on-farm, off-farm, and employment). FY 2020 funds will continue supporting access to tailored financial services and livelihood options as well as expand access to markets. The activity will focus on building youth capacity and skills and linking them to employment opportunities through information sharing and networks. .In FY 2020, the activity enters its final year with more focus on consolidation, sustainability, and exit strategies. The Activity will work with Livelihood Groups (LGs) participating in Savings and Internal Lending Communities (SILC) to mobilize internal financial resources as well as leverage external financing. More effort will be made to help youth and women to build their capacity and skills. LRO will support two aspects of nutrition security: production of nutrient-dense agricultural products and improved food utilization. LG members will be trained, in line with COVID-19 requirements, in how to produce and prepare nutritious foods, and facilitate cooking demonstrations. Household based perma-gardening, a small-scale, high-yield, gardening approach that conserves water and improves soil fertility will also be promoted...The activity will implement a poultry voucher strategy, a market-oriented scheme designed to jump-start poultry value chain participation, to both improve the nutritional status of households and increase household incomes. In addition to continuing implementing interventions approved in response to COVID-19, in FY 2020 the activity will consider if any additional support is needed in response to shocks to protect food and nutrition gains already made. ..
